{# Plan 33: shared evaluation-context partial used by every prompt that
   needs to render the four-stage audit rubric verbatim. Three macros:

   * ec_full(contract)                   — all four stage cards (planner,
                                            fixup-planner, merge-planner)
   * ec_stage_card(contract, stage_name) — one stage card (subtask-doer
                                            renders four times in order)
   * ec_targeted(contract, subtask)      — only the rubric_targets,
                                            standards_referenced, and
                                            behavior_evidence_advanced
                                            this subtask owns; plus the
                                            always-on local_ci card
                                            (subtask-checker + triage)

   StrictUndefined is enabled in `quikode/prompts.py:25` — missing
   contract fields fail loudly at render time, never silently empty. #}

